    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-09T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-09T12:00:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4557: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-09T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 9, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 10—2:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3261. Boheman<note n="41" xml:id="d369fn41">E. C. Boheman, Swedish Minister for
                        Foreign Affairs.</note> has just informed that number of Danish refugees now
                    in Sweden has reached 6000, 1800 having arrived within last 24 hours. Of the
                    total number fully 90% are Jews. He said that there are approximately 6000 Jews
                    registered in Denmark as of Hebrew faith. Number of Jews unregistered because of
                    belonging officially to no faith or conversion to Christianity is not known but
                    he does not believe number is great. Germans have not yet made any reply to
                    Swedish <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> (my 3149, September 30, 10 p.m.) and
                    Boheman doubts that any reply will be made. Increase in press articles in
                    Germany attacking Sweden he thinks are in fact directed and constitute a form of
                    reply to Swedish protest. Boheman regrets violence of Swedish press comment and
                    attacks on Germany which he thinks unnecessary and blustery as logical
                    conclusion of such attacks would mean a Swedish declaration of war on Germany
                    which is out of question. He remarked, that in view of fact almost entire Jewish
                    population of Denmark is now in Sweden, objective of Swedish <hi rend="italic"
                        >démarche</hi> in Berlin has been attained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
